 That was a regular thing. My mother used - I used to go in front because she didn't want people to know where she was going. And my mother - very few women went to work, they were slaves to
 the home weren't they, and I remember our room was all beds, it was one room, and I remember the furniture out in the garden, I presume because they had no rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you remember being evicted as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. I - I do remember that, and I was l
ooked after by a very nice old couple who had no children. They looked after me. They lived down the stairs in the house, a boot repairer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 named}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6577362\charrsid7632643 Mr.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 Winch. They looked after me, fed me and slept down there with them. And then through my mother joining a mot
hers union, a mother's union, that's right, she eventually got my father a job. And - I was informed that they had found out he was such a brilliant joiner and staircase }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  that - he was there many}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  many years after that, and they had some economic securi
ty. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
nfortunately he was a great drinker you see. My mother used to tell me nearly every weekend - used to hold our arms and go round from pub to pub looking for him. And she used to say to me, if I ever saw a fight in the street outside a pub, which w
ere many, she'd say, I'll be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  that's my Jim. And she was nearly always - true. And there you are you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 There weren't so many other recreations for working men in those days were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well the cinema was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 , come out for a packet of swee
ts, and there was clubs and turns, you know, old time - what they used to call old time variety. And - the public was their chief place to go. I used to sit outside, I used to sit outside. They're uncouth places really. And - people there I suppose were s
o
 loaded up with poverty that they done anything for - for escapism you see. And I remember one - I also remember when the M.P. - when there was a Parliament down, the men used to come round a kiss the babies, they used to call it a kiss the baby tour, you
 know, if they get the votes you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 Most working class people were Tory, mind you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well they said that you must have the rich you see. They didn't think that rich must have you too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 She was around my father's age, twenty-six - twenty-five, that's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 My - my mother came from a place called Packenham Street in Essex Road, Islington. Right near the old Collins Music Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, she told me she worked in a factory. And I can't recall what factory it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did she work at all after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Only when the 1914/18 war started, then she - then she - all women - most women got a job. A 
terrible job she had. She used to come home like a sweep, black, they was putting something in these batteries for lamps. Batteries. Something like that. I remember coming home all filthy dirty and black, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 But apart from that she didn't do any part time work or casual work?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
To my knowledge very few women did. As you know they were very prolific them days, they had a - had a child every year, most of them, you know, through ignorance as you know and - birth control was non-existent then. And I
 remember Doctor Marie Stopes opening her first birth control clinic opposite where I lived.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Ten. I think I was. And I remember the women, the narrow minded bigoted women having a protest how disgusting it was you see. Al
though it's probably more disgusting to have children you couldn't - you - you - you had, couldn't bring them up in a high standard }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 physiologically}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  and physically you see. And I think that the place is still there. That's in Marlborough Road, Holloway. Mar
lborough Road. Doctor Marie Stopes. And that opened - 'cos at ten I didn't understand what it was all about, but I know now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This place you lived in Islington, was it one room only or one room with a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, one room and a backroom. One room and a back room. The - furniture was practically }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 negligible}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
. I remember all the beds - 'cos I was forced to sleep with my sisters. I used to - my three sisters slept at the top and I remember sleeping - more to our shame - I used to sleep at the bottom, crossways, yes. That's all there was. There was no}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 thing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  else }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  us to do you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And this backroom was where you did the cooking and this sort of thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 As you were so crowded you didn't have any lodgers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Not to my knowledge, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 It - no, no, in a big copper. Wash 'til midnight. Wash 'til midnight. Slaves - handcuffe
d to the washtub. All they knew was poverty, anguish and work. And sometimes it's understandable why they got a little drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Mostly secondhand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 a lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  were bought at 
pawn shops, and if they - if it was comparatively new they'd buy so much a week put down-and - I can't remember the prices of clothes. I don't remember - I don't remember. And the lady downstairs used to make me trousers. I used to wear button up boots. Y
es.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother ever make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did she or your father repair clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I suppose she done the usual sewing in the home but not to my - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about shoes, were they new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - I can tel
l you that lots of children - were shabby old shoes left down from their brothers, and furthermore - I remember my - schoolmaster, who I considered was a - intellectual tyrant towards us, he hadn't got an ounce of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 psychology}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 , some of the children - he used
 to say, where were you yesterday? They'd say, we couldn't come to school sir, because we had no boots to wear. In the winter. He used to say to them - you must not break the law, you've got to come to school, wrap rag round your feet. Now there was his w
ords, and I remember them as if they were said today, yesterday, that's what he said. He was a B.A. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 
That was only a label attached to him because to me he wasn't an honest man, but he was - very, very - very rigid and firm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. And I remember saying to the
 boys - you must not - you must come to school whether you've got boots on or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How old were you when you started going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You started around - when you started around - I think you started about five - or six. Very young. Five - I think it was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When you first started going to school was it full time or half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh no, full time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember what the school hours were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 About nine 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Had you been given any lessons before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 None at all. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What kind of school was it, was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, a board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was this mixed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Up to a certain age were mixed, then you're transferred to boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 About what age would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Tennish. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How long did it take you to get to school from where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh only about a few minutes. Lived in the same road. Cottenham Road, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you just used to go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you have your midday meal when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 We could come back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you usually have at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well, the lady downstairs who looked after me, we used to have a lot of sop, bread and milk. I remember that well. Bread and milk 
soup. I remember that well. Distinctly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did this lady downstairs look after you quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Very well indeed. She had no children of her own and she kind of - I guess she wanted me down there really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did she used to take your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, used to look after the sisters, brought us presents. Yes. Oh yes I remember her well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When I was at school I was very happy, I was very academically minded you know. I was very h
appy. When I look back on my schooldays I - I would say that what they taught me was really reading, writing, arithmetic, religion, and - glorifying war. I must put that in 'cos it's true. On Empire Days we used to have a Brigadier General Cooper used to 
come. And we all held Union Jacks you know. The cause of war was never introduced to us. I remember the Empire Days very well indeed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 These were always a big patriotic occasion were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well, yes, they used to glorify the war you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How did you feel about the teachers in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well the teachers didn't have a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 psychology}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  them days 'cos I remember distinctly - one teacher used to punish you by putting your hand on a table and holding it with his other - wrist and smashi
ng your fingers with a ruler, I remember him. And I had the cane - I had the cane for something I was entirely innocent. It was - I didn't make these noise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  in class but I was brought out and six lashes on the - and it wasn't me at all. But they had no time for explanation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was discipline fairly strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Very strict indeed, yes. You had no chance to explain yourself or - thought you was a hum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 n being and of course - we - I would say mainly our schooling was a - instruction on the basis of a lot of
 fear. Instead of understanding your master - we used to fear them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did the class masters used to cane you or did you have to go to the head for the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
he head man. What}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7632643  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 remember - out in the hall, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did the classroom teachers box your ears and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, that's - they done that, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What other punishments did they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I've only known that, very - with teachers - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 asty teacher hit you round the legs with it. Round the legs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about lines and keeping you in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - I've done lines and - they used to make you stand in a corner. Stand in a corner, yes. Very embarrassing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did they used to punish the girls the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I wouldn't know. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
No, I said before, no, they did not. Now I'll try and remember - as I said, it was prayers, religion, history, wars, reading, writing and arithmetic. And singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 None to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did they ever visit the school or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Only on Empire Day, once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 This was a parents' day as well was it?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well it was a common thing, you had got to go to school so go to school, and - they never came, I don't remember anything like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were the other children from similar types of home to yourself or was it a mixed area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, no, all similar. All - all the area, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 The only treat - you mean - medicinal or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Just in their general treatment of dealing with people, did they have favourites and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember any favourites, no. Collectively they just - taught you. Full of orthodoxy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were there any gangs amongst the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Only in sport. In the playground. - The gangs were overbacks, and football and cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever go on to a different school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I kept there 'til I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you have stayed any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I wanted to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 None at all. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
About what? Well although I think regretting's a foolish philosophy, but at the same time - I do. Because they didn't - care much about the child, it was - very elementary rudiments 
they taught you, and there wasn't a great interest in your future, not really, as you left someone else took your place you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 I'll put it like this, the psychology they had was very little.
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you were glad to leave when the time came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, and my mother also for the little money. My first job was at ten bob a week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you think you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh well, yes, I mean if I didn't go to school at all I - I - couldn't probably even read or write could I, so yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 He wouldn't wash up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Help himself to pints of beer, that's what his favourite pastime was. Didn't stand alone. Great drinkers them days you know, well - the }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 home life}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
, they wanted to get out and escape from it. And the mother was - the mother with the children was - handcuffed. No emancipation at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have - or your sisters - have any regular tasks to carry out in the home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well they helped washing up and similar things but then they, like teenagers today, when they were - got a little older they was out. Mostly courting, you know how it goes. Yes. I used to help a lot in the home with my mother. I did. A great erra
nd runner. Getting errands for her you see. All on the weekly, never had the money to give you see, pay the end of the week. That was accepted thing you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This was a matter of running errands when your mother wanted something - you know, sometimes it was one child's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 duty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  to clean the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Exactly. Well my parents weren't very strict: I would say my parents were apathetic, not unkind. They were apathetic. I know my father's favourite - career was the - drinking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 As the younger children were growing up did the older children have to help them or have to look after the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh yes. Oh yes, sit in and look after - when my mother and father used to go to the cinema my job was to - to stay in and - oh yes. I remember that 
well, when they - even when they went out to parties, my job was to stay and look after them you see, being the eldest, I remember that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 At what age would you start doing this, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh when I - I was about ten - twelve. Eight to twelve. Yes, sure. Sure, sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time during your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Expected to, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Can you remember the time or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh probably eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed or did you get yourselves off to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I think I got myself off to bed. I - I - I'm not boasting, I don't remember giving my mother any trouble. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I suppose it was difficult for the children to get to sleep with all living in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I can't recall every incident thing but I - I do remember - all sleeping in one bed. I remember that clearly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents sleep in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, they slept in a front room. They had a room - a f
ront - you see, where I slept was where they done the cooking. And this house I'm referring to now is just being pulled down right now, after all them sixty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So the children slept in the back room and your mother and father slept in the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In the front room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh - they didn't exist. Oh, we - oh I see what you mean. Oh we used to bath in the - in the kitchen in front of the fire in an old enamel bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How often was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I suppose - I'm only assuming - about once a week I suppose you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well that's - when we had clean clothes. I suppose our - shirts was changed once or twice a week - my mother was always at the wash tub. I know t
hat. If I wanted her she was down at the wash tub. In the winter too. No protection you know. They was out in the - yard. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about the toilet facilities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well if I remember that was out - all out in the open - these yards were - only - 
only about four or six feet - wide, you know. Oh yes. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 back gardens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 backed on to each other. Like they do in the North. Like the North, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you usually have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In this back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever eat in the other room at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Not to my knowledge, no, we used the back kitchen, we all used to sit round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of cooking equipment did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh now let me think, it was a very old fashioned gas stove. Very old fashioned gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When was breakfast eaten, what time was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I guess we start - I suppose about eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were all the family there together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I remember we used to have that old sop. I 
remember that - bread and milk, with sugar, I remember that, that was a staid diet. Sop and milk, and - and - and I had - they used to give me a lot of currants to eat, I remember my - me currants. But I remember the sop, I remember that. Stews. Well - ch
eap you see. Save the stew what left over from ma, I would assume that they was cheap. I forget the cost of commodities them days, but they was ha'penny and penny, you know that, ha'penny and penny they were. I remember the cinema was a penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When did you have your main cooked meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh I suppose a - around - when we come home from school, about half past twelve. Generally the accepted time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You'd have it midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of things would you have in the evening, after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh I remember - bread and jam, bread and jam, lot of that went - bread and jam. All for cheapness you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What would your father have when he came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I - I - to be truthful I can't remember what he used to eat
, I know he used to eat a lot of kippers, that's it. Kippers. Kippers. Bloaters. Penny ha'penny a pair I think they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When did he have his main cooked meal though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well he generally had it when he was at work you see. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When he'd come home in the evening he'd have kippers or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - I know kippers was top of the bill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I remember we used to have a - bit of meat if you could get it. Yes, we'd have a - Sund
ay meals a bit of a holiday, something to look forward to you know. Traditional, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you have something different fro Breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I think still - no, midday meal was the thing we looked forward to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would Sunday tea be any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - well I used to have my tea downstairs with the lady, they used to look after me for years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother bake her own bread or make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about making pickles or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Nothing. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You couldn't grow any fruit and vegetables could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Stone. Wasn't at big as this room. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did they buy tinned or dried vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh no, no tins. I don't remember tinned vegetables when I was a lad. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I used to keep rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were these kept for food or as pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh no, just for - pets. Rabbits, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well if I remember I - I - I think it - I think it was about once or twice a week, not - well the money wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I never remember tinned food when I was young, I don't remember it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. I never saw that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 My people wasn't extremely strict. No, no. No. They weren't. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 They}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  weren't strict, no, no, no. My father was a kind man outside of his - everybody has something, they've got some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 idiosyncrasy}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  but - he was a kind man and I say - he was practically nearly an alcoholic you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 During meals could you choose what you wanted from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Ladled up in front of you and you just ate it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What would their attitude be if you left something uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I'll tell you what a lot of mothers used to say, now you do not leave the table 'til you eat it. Which is foolish and unwise - bad. Because if a child's had enough it's had
 enough. Even an animal walks away doesn't it? But they never saw it that way. They say, now look here, you've got to eat that. And the poor child could have a stomachache afterwards. But that was through ignorance you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask for it or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well generally - as a boy, keep }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  place. Even if you was in the right, still keep your place. That was one of the - platitudes of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So if you wanted it how would you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Just ask for it. The salt mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Could you ask for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 second helping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - I guess you could, whether there was any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 There was no guarantee that you'd get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Me - like - I think if you want to eat peas with a fork - a fork - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 knife}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  I don't see why you shouldn't. Not doing anybod
y any harm are you? But the idea was you'd had an accident you see. Yes, they - one of them used to smack my hand you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When could you leave the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well as far as I remember, my family, you could leave when you wanted to, but in many families you could only leave when you was told to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did all the family sit down at the table together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you always sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I - I - no. Get - run in and get where you can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh my father first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Then who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - father first and all of us and we started. No-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When there were babies in the family where were they fed before they could sit up and eat at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - I can only remember my youngest sister being born, me standing by the bed - but I can't recall - that's all 
I remember of my youngest sister. I can remember it now - no I can't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Very nice woman. I - my - my mother was a nice - nice woman. She - stood up to adversity very well indeed. She use
d to cry and break down, but she didn't stand alone. And I think they had so much poverty that they lived with it and accepted it. They didn't know anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If you had any worries as a child would you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I used to share them with her and the lady downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was your mother an affectionate person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 A what? Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. I think we were left a lot to go ou
r own way you know. I used to go out and - I joined a gymnasium when I was about - ten. And I lived in one 'til I was nearly fifteen. Well - when you've one on sport I'll let you know that later on if you want to know what I was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well generally do as you're told. That's what I'd put it like that, do - do as you was told. Whether it was right or wrong didn't come into it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
They never said to me - my father said to me once - he said, you're a - sport man, son. And he wanted me to learn a trade you see. - Well I went with him as a - joiner, a woodcarver, my mind wasn't there. I wanted to be something e
lse. And I reached that position that I wanted to be. He didn't want me to be that, he wanted me to be what he wanted you see. As you know, most sons follow their father's trade. - Even if they didn't want to be that. If you're father's a dustman I don't 
see why he should make his boy be one. 'Course necessity knew no law them days, you were glad - glad to get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No, not - not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If another child hurt you did they teach you to hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
My father used to teach me to - well - you're coming to something I want to tell you later on. My father used to teach me to - always - retaliate with - brute force you see. 'Cos he fancied his - fancied himself
 as a street fighter. And I've got my - I've got my views on - on violence and - I think what we call morality decided by the motive. There's certain things that I would do under given circumstance - circumstances I wouldn't do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So as a child you were encouraged to stand up for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Go out and fight him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well they didn't like it, I - I - no one's a saint I know, I suppose - I don't remember swearing much at all when I was a boy. I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents swear at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Well they - they nearly all did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. As a boy - as a boy keep your place. You may be able to teach them something but it doesn't
 matter. You keep your place - as a boy. It's the other way round now. Tell the parents to keep their place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If your parents did something you disproved of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7632643  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - as I say, not my business. No, oh no, no, no, you had no say in it,
 my - my father - the father - generally - I'm generalizing now, the father's law - the father's word was law in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If they disapproved of what you were doing you'd get punished would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Not physically. Not always physically, no, depends what I was doing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 
As I said, I - I wasn't a little saint but with my trend towards - a certain type of sport I never bothered them, I never got in trouble in the street because I - most of my time was spent in the gymnasium - of an evening. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And there you are you see, where if I was hanging around the streets loose - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 Satan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 finds work for idle hands to do. I don't believe in all these sayings, they don't ring true to life, but that one I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Can you remember any occasion at all when you were punished by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well, yes, I do. I do - I do one. My mother's at the washtub, she must have been exceedingly tired and worn out, and I remember washing in this old cold backyard and I must have gone down and bothering her. And then - in a little fit 
of temper she hit round the mouth. And I know her ring caught my moth. And yet when a master hit me she went up the school and stormed about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So they didn't use corporal punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, - no, no, no. Definitely not. No. Definitely not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I don't remember him hitting me. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 It was usually your mother was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - it's not impossible if I was a woman and I was - she didn't - she didn't do it with venom. I don't - I can't think of h
er like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you say that the ideas that you had about how to behave came from both your parents or was one more important than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Neither of them. I - I got a - I slowly - came to the decision myself by reasoning. You know, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Who would you say was most important when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Your father would be the influence while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. My father - my mother was bowed down by worry. Most women were. And when you've got extreme worry yo
u can't think very logically can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would your birthday be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh birthdays, yes, I used to have some nice presents given me from the lady - downstairs. One of the presents were things like called a monkey up a st
ick. It was very fascinating, you went like that and the monkey swing off the stick. And - Christmas night was a revelation. I remember laying in bed one night and I would-not go to sleep, by the chimney waiting for alleged Father Christmas to come down. 
I remember that. And I remember my father dressing up as Father Christmas, coming in my room and - laying the - where ignorance is bliss it's folly to be wise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you do on Christmas Day with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh, we had - we'd jolly - we used to have - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  with the - cylinder records. And we all used to have to stand round the trumpet, all listening, it was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 unorthodox}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 . The Edison Bell record it was called. And funny little record like, whitewashing the Ceiling and Building a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 Chicken house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
. The star of the day was a man named Fred Evans who done all that kind of thing. Yes. Then when we used to have the parties Christmas Day, we had no piano or nothing. Although I'm a pianist myself you see. We had no piano and they used to - all the 
people used to sit on the edge of the bed, and get up and sing and make their own - enjoyment kind of thing. Plus plenty of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you get presents on your birthday from your parents as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - that depends if they had any money. A penny toy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 you'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  jump for joy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have a birthday cake or anything like this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember that at all. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents play any games with you while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. I remember one game they used to play with us, a
 game called hiding the thimble. My mother used to - we'd all go out the room and my mother would hide a thimble in the room, hide it anywhere. Then we all come in and as we got near to this - place where the thimble was hidden my mother would say, you're
 
getting warmer, you're getting warmer. And if you walked away from it she'd say, you're getting colder, colder, colder. Now I had a sister used to hide a thimble and she used to get so excited that when you got near she used to say, here it is, she used t
o tell you. Spoiled it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were there any books in the house while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No books. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about newspapers or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well my father - my father used to read a book called - oh dear, I can't think of it now - Answe
rs, that's the name of the book, a book called Answers, similar to Tit-Bits today. Them kind of books, yes, he used to read them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't - no, used to go across the road and get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Yes I do. My young brother was three months old, and - they used to place the coffin under the driver's feet. Well he was above. That was a time - the only time the working people had money spent on 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Could you tell us what you remember about this funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I can. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have special clothes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember about the clothes but I was probably around about ; he was th
ree months, I must have been about four - three, four. I remember it was a gig affair for the neighbours because it was something of important to them although they had no feeling, and they stand outside their house for hours waiting. And - they - I - I h
ad - used to have a feeling that they had a little - it was bit of entertainment for them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of hears did you have, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, one hearse, one - like an old brake, an old fashioned hansom cab, that's it. The horses were dre
ssed with big black bunches on their head they used to have and long black - velvet gowns over their body.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Yes. Yes I was, I was taken out - I used to go to my aunt and uncle at Walthamstow - 
yes. And - and then I was - used to see an old lady at that - she was ninety in her age when I was about four, name of Mrs Gentle, and then we used to go to Southend, and I might remind you the fare - to Southend and back was one and nine return. That's w
hat it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was this Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I presume it was holiday time when my father had the money you see. I know it was one and nine return fare. That's what it was. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes I do. Use
d to go a place called the World's Fair, the Agricultural Hall, Upper Street, Islington, where we used to have the circuses, trapeze artists, Jugglers, strong men, side shows, we used to go there regular. About tuppence or threepence or sixpence, I'm not 
- yes. I remember that with great delight. Remember that. The hall is still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So as a child your parents would take you to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Only to through the benevolence of the lady downstairs and her husband and - they helped a lot. Hadn't be
en for them we probably wouldn't have - gone any place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Could you tell me a bit more about these two people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well, he - yes, they had the ground floor, he was a boot repairer them days on the whole. And when we moved there I presume that they we
re childless and I was the eldest and - then - they must have took a liking to me. I remember buying me what is known as a bicycle horse. You sit on it. And I remember the first Sunday I had it they cleared all the furniture out the front room and I remem
ber going round and round this room all day long, I wouldn't get off of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This was his own shop was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's right, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13124176\charrsid7632643 his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  workshop, yes, they used to charge around one and six to do your shoes up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were your shoes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well - I had no brothers, as I said before, I was very lucky to have - the people downstairs who were childless took a kind of liking to me and they looked after me, so - I didn't have the trouble that other children had - when there's bigger families. I 
had no brothers so I couldn't wear - the cast offs could I. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 These people downstairs would even buy you a pair of shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh they looked after me, I was - pretty well dressed for a kid them days, I remember. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father have much to do with you, would he tell you stories or read to you or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
His great - greatest pastime was - in the public house. But he did used to tell me stories of his - boxing ability. And I always used to - I smile now - he never appeared
 to lose, always used to win. But I think he was a romancer. He used to tell me about - he never told me about the fights my mother told me he'd had outside the public houses. She used to look for him with me in her arms, so she told me, and when she saw 
a crowd outside a pub and there was a fight it was generally Jim. 'Cos that the common thing in them Saturday nights you know, they used to - used to - used to enjoy it - better than paying five guineas for a ringside seat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would he ever look after you while your mother went out or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't recall that. My mother - no, I never recall that at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 At mealtime how was the meal served, some people take the plates to the stove, some people bring the food to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 We had a 
gas stove right near the table. And she used to fetch it in the plate. Mostly stews or - mostly. From the gas stove to the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, he was O.K. but - he never used to seem to take a great intere
st in me. No sooner he was in he was out, I recall that. Even - even when we went to parties, soon as he got in the place I used to remember one of his sayings was - come on up to have a drink. And my job was to look after all the kids in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So if company came round he'd still be out?
\par 
