\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 To my knowledge, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Or your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, most - most men them days, not all, were Conservatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You don't remember your father voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well on the general election they call it now kiss the baby tour don't they, in America they call it that. They used to come round, a man name of Mr Touch, he got in every yea
r. Every year he - he got elected. And - the Labour people and the Socialist people - were - were - mostly on the platform but they never got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You don't remember your father taking any part in this at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh I said - all I remember him saying, you must have the rich. But he never told me how they got rich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you assume he was a Conservative if he voted at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 He was a working class Tory, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well my moth
er - one of my mother's - in the summer my mother always sitting at the window, and she used to sing to herself. And I used to play with the other kids in the street, all kinds of games. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 
Games called - overbacks, Jimmy Nacker and Tibbycat and release and running round the houses, all them games. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
And was exceedingly happy Very little money we had, money didn't come into it. I didn't realize the poverty, you do not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well she did join a mother
s meeting. She did. And that's why my father was fortunate enough to get the regular job - after all them years in and out, in and out, in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember any of the details of this mothers union at all, how often she went or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I - I - I know where it was but I - I don't know - I never went there. No. I don't know anything about that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 She used to go to the cinema with my father. By the way she behaved and other wo
men too in a cinema they - they used to live with it, they used to talk to the actors. She used to say to 'em, look behind you, and - he never done it. He done it, you see, it was very good indeed. They lived with it. Well I remember my mother coming out 
the cinema with my father and I was very - very young and I remember what she said to him she said, Jim - she should have never married that man, he'll never be any good to her. Now that's what I call - living with a picture, that is true. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How often would they go to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh once or twice a week. People used to really cry at the cinema them days, when the lights went up you look round - see 'em all tears down their eyes you see. Used to snivel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What time did your father get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well - he used to work on several building jobs, I can't answer that in truth - and I remember once he went away to Penge to work, you see. Well - well in the building trade it was the worst trade to be in for in - for inconsistency.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If he was working close at hand how many evenings a week would he be at home indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Very seldom - always - no, he was very seldom at home. No, he was in the public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother ever go to the public house with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
No, he only used to talk about it, I never heard - I've never known him to go in - in for - in for any - any particular sport. No. He used to follow the boxing in them days you kno
w, boxing was very prevalent them days. But - to my knowledge, I - never known him to participate as an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 amateur}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 or professional. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would he go to watch boxing matches and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did he ever go to the races or have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Not to my - no, I - I think - I don't think - no. No. I think by the time he paid my mother and by the time he had his drink he was ready for pay day again. I - I can't recall in fact what it was like but it must have been sores than - 
or worse - it was - terrible existence you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, any sick clubs or funeral clubs, anything like this do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I think they used to belong to some little - ha'penny or penny a week club,
 I think they did now, yes. Used to be run by the public houses, I forget what they used to call them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This would be a slate club wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's it, that's the word. Slate club, they belonged to that. That's right. That's it. Sure. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You don't think they belonged to anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You mentioned one time you just remember seeing the furniture in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In - in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was this in Highgate or in Islington do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This was in - Islington. We
ll Highgate is Islington. As a borough, another part of it. This was in the slummy place we lived. And it - they've just started to pull them down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This was before you went to the place where the people lived underneath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, that was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You were actually evicted from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, yes, that is from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you move to from there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 From there we went to - a place called Duncan Road, and from Duncan Road we went to a place called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 Marlborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  Road and - right opposite where Doctor Marie Stopes opened her first - birth control - shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you had three moves before 1918 in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - yes. Cottenham Road, Duncan Road - Marlborough Road and then - Hickeray Road where I spent my boy - my teenage days - up to
 I was about - twenty-eight. And my mother died in - this street. I was sent by the Bureau to get a job as a hod carrier and when I come back I was pleased I'd got it, and when I got to the house the lady said, there's been a terrible shock for you Jimmy,
 and I went indoors and - my mother was dead you see, I was twenty-six and she was fifty-one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When you moved from above the boot repairer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3300048\charrsid7632643 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 s you still kept contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Yes. Oh well, when we moved from Marlborough Road they came with u
s. Yes. They came with us. Then the old lady died and the old gentleman died so - we went - my mother and father used to move with them. Or they moved with us you know. Kept together, the four, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So they died in your boyhood did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How did you get on with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 All right. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was there any one of them you felt particularly close to or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. The one that died. The one that died. I used to get on very well with her. The eldest sister. Bu
t I get on very well with my sisters, I have two alive right now. I don't see - I only see them now and again, they live a long way away you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 As a child who did you play with, your sisters or neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I used to play around with j
ust - play - play with my sisters indoors - indoor games. We used to go to the magic lanterns a lot, I remember, the magic lanterns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Who used to run those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 They used to run those at the - the Sunday school, Bury, a place called Bury, yes. I can 
recall what they were like, used to get thrilled with these little pictures of men jumping over chairs and - that's all it consisted of you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you play as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In the street outside the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you go to local parks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Mostly in the streets, street games. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I guess so, I suppose my mother used to reprimand me and every - yes, but - I used to play athletic games mostly, I know what I used to play you know. As I told you, I've - mentioned it before, the names of the games, oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have money of your own to spend while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Pennies and ha'pennies and - penny, ha'penny, very seldom more than a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you used to spend this on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Sweets. If I had it, sweets. But I used to have my dinner and go and play and have me tea, so money didn't come into it a great deal.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have to pay to go into the swimming baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Two pennies I think. Yes, tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So your parents would give you money for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 My mother was always in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No one used to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 If your mother was ill or confined to bed, for example when your sisters were born, how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh we used to have an aunt come down and see - an aunt called Auntie Polly, she used to come round, but I can't recall my mother b
eing ill. I can't recall it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - not near - yes. My - my father's father and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  mother lived close by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And this Auntie Polly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 She lived close by. She lived around - in Islington. And my - other - the only aunt I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 lived}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  at Walthamstow, we used to visit them occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you see much of the relatives in Islington? Your father's people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Used to go Sunday mornings to my grandfather. Used to go and see him and my gr
andmother. They were more well off than we were. He was an optician by - by - by profession. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You always used to visit them at their home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, they never come to see us, not to my knowledge, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did they used to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh they used to come home and then - or - or see them in the pub, public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, I think - yes, yes, they did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 One or two women friends used to come and - have a chat with her. I remember 'em coming, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where would she see these women friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In our room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Just at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 She wouldn't go out to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
No, in the front room. We used to visit our Aunt Polly in Hornsey Road, Islington, Holloway. I used to remember going round with her, yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How often would you say friends would come in to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh periodically, no particular time, they'd come from across the road and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 They'd just call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
People were like then you know, they used to leave their door - lot of - they had the door open all day you know and they - and - do you know where I live now t
here's people next door don't know you. They had the door open most - in the summer. And sitting on the steps used to do on chairs people you know - and talk. As far as I can remember, yes, and the kids played in the street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So people would call in without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 This would be friends and neighbours }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 would it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Yes, used to call in. All used to sit in the door in the summers evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would people who were invited in be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, a cup of tea generally was, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you say the friends that were invited in were mainly your mother's or mainly father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Both. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents ever go to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Relatives. My - my - uncle and aunt. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 neighbours? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Mostly they had parties and singing, people would get up and sing and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 
gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 was a great thing then days. Though you couldn't bear it now with a - used to be cylinder records and - to find out what they were saying you had to stand right up against the trumpet. One or two are still exis
tence in antique shops as you know. It was called the Edison Bell record. And - you couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 discern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  some of the words at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So if friends came round it would be a bit of a sing-song?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's right, and beer. And a talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did they ever play any games, card games or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember that. Sometimes - generally come round to borrow a tanner - six - pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Many people divide society into different social classes, in that time before 1918 did you think of some peop
le as belonging to one class and some to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well most of the people what I remember - weren't very - bright or intellectual 'cos their - their education was so - what can I say - primitive. The sum total of the education of the average person 
when I was at school - is reading and writing and arithmetic and that's all. There }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 were no grants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
, no stopping at school 'til you're nineteen. As a matter of fact my mother was only too pleased when I left school, to earn a little money for her you see. At least I finished school could read and write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 you would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  say the different classes were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I there was extremely rich and extremely poor. And let me say this, I would say - what you term - I don't like this word middle clas
s, probably - bank clerks - and people in Government jobs or local Government jobs but - I do know one thing, it was extremely rich and extremely poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Which class }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 you would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 The extremely poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 you would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  say belonged to that same class as yourself, what sort of occupations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh - journeymen, tradesmen, builders, bricklayers - transport men, similar today - a man who had a job on the borough council was a - he was very well satisfied with himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Who would you put in the very rich class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - the Lords - the landowners, the Lords - what - what called the aristocrats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where would you put shopkeepers in this class business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What - the shopkeepers that looked after - 
the shopkeeper that served us was a - just a working man himself, 'cos I'm sure he had a lot of debts 'cos people used to go and have all stuff on - pay the end of the week. 'Course Selfridges and Derry and Toms, they were - I think they were still functi
oning them days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 The ones who weren't much better off were the corner shops were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's it, you've got it, the corner shops, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You think these were more working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 - they used to give you the stuff for fear of losing your custom altogether you see. There was no competition them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where would you put clergymen in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well - clergymen were very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 cozy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  and snug weren't they, they are today. Now I don't want to tread on religion, I have my personal view of - orthodoxy. But they used to preach to people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 
\endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 negative philosophy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 while they - their bread was buttered. I wouldn't preach to a man religion if he was - belly was hungry. I would feed him first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about teachers, where would you put them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well the teachers were a little - elevated to what I would call the - real working class. I suppose their money touched about - there pounds a week I guess where the average man was a guinea. They were secure as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So which class would you say they were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well just a little level above the working class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about a bank clerk or a white collar job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well it depends what the - what - what post he has I guess }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 doesn\rquote t}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  it. He was just a working man really wasn't he, struggling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't suppose you met any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How about employers, where would you put them as a class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I put them as a class - a lot of them, not all, were tyrants. You'd get sacked for the least thing. You had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 them, and you had to knock at the door cap in hand and if you was late - you'd have to come back when they sent for you. I can tell you something about the employers on the railway 'cos during the war I was conscripted as a railway fireman and
 some very old drivers told me that when they were youngsters if they were late they'd have to come back when sent for. I believe that too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well yes, I was - I was told by my father that - the rich should be bowed to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  they were your superiors. Which - sometime probably morally and mentally they could be my inferiors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you taught to touch your cap or show respect in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Stand at attention, take your cap off. And - speak when you're spoken to. That was one of the things they taught us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Who were you taught to do this to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I suppose your - your employer or your foreman or your Sunday school teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was there anyone you called sir or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, when you was at work, when I - yes sir, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I can't recall anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I think mainly - you mean in my class of society? Well the rich went to church, they mostly went to church. And the poor - percentage - the poor people like - like of my class - were sent to church because it was the thing to do, the tradition to it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you say there was any difference between the church people and the chapel people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I think the - the church people were extremely dogmatic. And my observation of some of the chapel people they 
were more like they are here you know. 'Cos here you know there are no conditions, you know that don't you. Mr Bryant is a very nice man. He never bothers you, and he never talks about religion. Don't come into it here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Practically, yes. Some a little - inferior to others but - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Oh definitely. There were the rough
s and the bullies and the street bullies. And the women used to fight. It was very frequent to see fights in the streets. Oh yes. You see a big crowd come along and they all used to stand and watch it. Not tell them to stop. And then the policeman would c
ome along and he'd - break it up and - if they was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 obstreperous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 they used to take them away on stretcher and strap them with a big hood. And we used to follow the stretcher along the street and keep looking in. And when they got them in the police station, 
if they heard a noise the crowd - would accuse the police of beating them up. Of course it may hot be true. Well, basically the people, they liked it, they liked to follow the - this - ambulance, it was an ambulance, a brown coloured ambulance, and inside
 was the unfortunate drunk. And they used to - wheel him to the station and pick him up on the stretcher and take - no carrying them through the streets, well today they have the van. That's how it was, mostly through drunks and fights.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What would you say was the main distinction between rough family and a respectable family in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well, I think most of the respectable working class families was based on - on - they had a religious atmosphere in the home you see. 'Cos I'm a man of no religion but I must accept that religion can play a part in the upbringing of the person. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you think it would be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 mainly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  religious inclination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's correct, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes - there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers. Lot of the craftsmen looked down on their labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well mother wasn't political
ly minded at all. Politics didn't exist to her. Her fight was getting enough money to feed us. As simple as that. And that was the beginning and end of it. I don't - she knew nothing about politics at all, and my father was a Tory and he used to say, you 
must have the rich otherwise we wouldn't get no work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, they wasn't conscious of that. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 One class to another? Providing you - you had to have the money first did you not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember any instance of anyone who did change from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't recall that, no. Most people were poor to the time they died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I did - hear a man called a - my father used to speak of a gentleman, a pugilist, Gentleman Jim. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 But I used to say, how can he be a gentleman if he'd punch people on the nose? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 He used to laugh at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You remember seeing the police around where you lived as a child, did you see many policemen in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh, quite - quite a few, they was generally all stereo typed, big black moustaches, and they used to
 use their capes to hit you with. Mind you they had a tough time. There - there was a road called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 Campbell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 Road, it's not in existence now, where they put the policemen down the drain upside down and he died. And no one ever found out who done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How do you think the police treated the people on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I don't - I don't really know, I never got in trouble with the police, only once, I was fined three shillings - for playing football in the street. Sunday afternoon. But the policeman told a lie. He was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643  probation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 policeman. The Magistrate was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
a North London Police Court, said, was it a busy thoroughfare? He said, very busy. Well it was the opposite. There was nobody - it was a quiet side street, one Sunday afternoon. But - it cost my father three shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you think of the police as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I - they - they didn't - we was all frightened of them - scared of them you know. Policemen. See, the uniform. Although was innocent, we used to be scared of them, but
 - I wasn't a saint but I always - I never got in any trouble, not to my knowledge, no. I never got into any trouble at all. Well I never got into any trouble you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you see anything of your landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, only heard of his name, never saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
I - was too young to bother about him, all I know he had a rent collector and - I know my mother said, can you call next week, that was a common thing I used to note. Can you call next - I think the rent was two and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember feeling as a child that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 conscious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  of it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
I never recall my father ill. When my father was out of work I used to hear my mother - see my mother cry. And my father used to say, I must get a job, I must get a job, I must get a job. Snow sweeping, anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did this happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Oh yes. We - we know that there was no dole, no Social Security. There were soup kitchens with the bowl of soup. And in the letter I gave you it tells you all about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I - I presume they did but I don't remember it. And I presume they did, yes. They used to give you a farthing breakfast. It don't seem possible, but I think it was a farthing. I don't know what they got, I never went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you don't really know whether your parents had help from the Guardians or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - with their tongue
. Oh yes, I can remember the women screaming at each other and - oh, tearing each other to pieces probably. And fight - I've seen fights with women. Yes, oh yes. They were crude you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember anyone being made to leave the district by anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 While you were at school did you have any part time jobs for means or earning any regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. I did. The man downstairs, the boot repairer, got me a job in a boot shop, taking out the repairs Saturday nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Was this in his boot shop?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. In another boot shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How old were you when you did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 About ten I think. Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How long did you do this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh I can't recall now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you do any other jobs like this while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And you just used to do this Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How long would this take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Depended how many - houses I had to call on with the shoe repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Could you tell me about your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
A friend of mine worked in the blacksmiths and he said, are you leaving school Jimmy? I said, yes. He said, well - Mr Barclay, the blacksmith, wants some - a boy, and I was fourteen an
d it was - just across the road from where I lived and I started. And the wages were ten shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you have to do in this job exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh - put pieces of iron together. Something to do with iron or metal, he was a smith you see. I wasn't there very long. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Do you remember what hours you worked on that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 They must have been about eight 'til six I think, or eight 'til seven, eight 'til six, yes, them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you feel that that was a fair wage or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't suppose it entered my head. It was just a bit of money to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How long did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I was there a week. I don't - a week, I was there a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Why did you leave there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I don't - I just left 'cos I wanted to I think, I - I know I was only there a week. That's all I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Then my father got me a job where he was working you see. And I worked with him and I - took the tools up as a joiner. But I was no good at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Were you apprenticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, no, no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You just started working with the tools and picking the trade up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 
Yes, and then I went out on the building jobs now and again you know - on the building jobs I went and then I - then my father got the regular job - through my mother, and was with him for a long, long while. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 'Cos he was made foreman because he was a good craftsman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So did you spend most of this time after leaving school in different jobs in the building grade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I went - no, I - then I got jobs working on the roads and the council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 First - when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You had several years on the building trade did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. From the blacksmith's jobs I got - I w
ent - I worked on - I worked with my father. Then I got jobs on the road, then I worked for piecework plasterer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
s, very hard work. I think it was about three pounds a week. I used to work all day long supplying plasterers with plaster on their boards. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 And then I - got a job with a steel erector's. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
I remember that job I done. 'Course the back of my mind was being a professional athlete all the time, that's what I wanted to be, eventually I succeeded in being one. And then I got this job on the golf course an
d I stayed there for many years, until I was - I was fit enough, what I considered good enough to be a professional wrestler you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You went as a golf caddy when you were about twenty-two years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Something - twenty-one or twenty-two, something like that, I can't recall exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 How old were you when you stopped being a golf caddy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well - I must have been around thirty, I'll tell you why, because - when I turned professional I - come to agreement with the promoters that I would on
ly wrestle in London so I wouldn't have to give up my golf caddying job. But - I appeared to be a fair success and I was given matches all over the country, and on the Continent, so I decided this is the life for me, and I gave up - the caddying entirely.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 You were a professional wrestler from then on were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 From - twenty-eight 'til I was forty-eight. Twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you do anything different between the war years or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Which war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 1939-'45?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well then I - I - I was a ra
ilway fireman, I - yes. I was conscripted by the National Central Works order, yes. I was trained as a locomotive fireman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What did you do after you finished professional wrestling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 After professional - well while I was a professional wrestling I was - a person asked me if I'd like a job. I said where is it? }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 On the borough of Holborn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And I - took a chance 'cos I was getting on in years and I went }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 for six months}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643  probation,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
 I stayed there for twenty-three years. This is this borough you see, which is now Camden. I worked this borough council twenty-three years you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 When did you start that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
When I was what - I was sixty - sixty-six when I left and I was - twenty-three years, I must have been forty - forty-three, that's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What sort of work was this?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I was a ro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 dent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  operative. Rodent. We used to - repress the rodent - rats you know. I used to go round with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 sewer man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  with - the poison, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 lowering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  it down the manholes in the road. And I was doing that
 all the time, nothing else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation than those you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I wanted to be a wrestler. A professional - a wrestler, that was - like a man dedicated to football you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So you really got the occupation you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 In the - oh yes, the National Union of Public Employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you take part in its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, for the meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I will say this of the borough council, they were - fine people to work for. They were very fine indeed. And I know the six months that - if there was any class distinction I never saw it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 What kind of - interest do you mean? What kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 The sort of division that you find between }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 craftsmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  and labourers, sometimes they feel more split than united?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I tell you what I found now, present day, the mentality that - dist - class distinction I think is practically gone. Yes, I think it has now because - when I first went to the borough council - if anybody in charge came on the scene they used to trem
b
le a little bit, but that's all gone. And I think there's very little discipline, and I don't think it's necessary, because on the council when I were there when you'd done your work you could go home. They didn't think there was any necessary - necessity
 to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
Well I felt a bit of a prisoner from the wrestling days 'cos I used to have most of the day to myself when I wasn't training. But - once you've been an 
athlete, doing something you want to do, any other jobs you take on is not so nice is it. 'Cos lots of people doing things for money alone, not 'cos they want to do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you continue to live at home when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 first}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  left school and started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Not at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Or with your sisters at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you spend your Sundays any differently after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 W
ell yes, I had money did I not, and I - I was a - great swimmer and in the summer I was always diving and sunbathing. I used to visit every day a place called Highgate Pond, Highgate. Yes. I never had much time for the West End and all them things. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you continue to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I - I'm Socialistically minded you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 
I realize the injustice in this world, of the haves and have-nots, but I must admit being truthful that - you compare the lot of the working man today and his lot years ago - he's in a very favourable - I know things are not perfect, I understand that. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 But when I look }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643  the pensions and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 ocial security, and look way back, well them people when I - my mother
 wouldn't have believed it, that she was going to get so much a week from the State.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you continue to spend your spare time in much the same way as you did when you were at school when you first left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Well I had more - I had more time to mix - among my athletic friends you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6361884\charrsid7632643 I used to visit gyms and train and - I was with a Japanese Judo wrestler's you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 
And - as some men are football crazy, some youths, and some are dog crazy and I was - what you call - wrestling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 So the only difference would be less street games and more athletics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes. Sure. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you used to go out in the evening, just after you left school and started work, did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, I made friends, oh sure, I
 - I'm - I remember making friends, yes, and - oh yes, I remember making friends. Going to pictures together. People used to go to cinema a lot you know. And then there was variety days, you know, there was always variety halls to go to you know. If you h
ad the money you'd no need to walk the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And you started going to these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Oh yes, I loved variety. I go now, still go now once a week, in town or - yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you ever bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes, I used to fetch some friends home, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have girl friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I - my - I think my first girl friend - real serious girl friend was the one I married, I was twenty-eight you see. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Where did you meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 I met her 
along the Embankment Gardens. I thought she was hard up and down and out and I asked if she needed any help. I remember giving her a meal and then I saw her again, you know how it goes don't you, and I - we got to like each other all right and - and that 
was that and - I was married twenty-three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did you have any special friends immediately after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Immediately left school? Oh yes, boy friends, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Not so much girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, not - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 And you'd go to the cinema and variety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13765166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15816399 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15882744\charrsid7632643 No, I never used to bring them home, one or two but not a lot, no, no.
